Parfait 🚀 Je vais te faire une structure hiérarchique prête à copier-coller pour Jira, en anglais (Épic → User Story → Acceptance Criteria).
Tu pourras l’utiliser comme guide pour créer tes tickets Jira.

⸻

📌 Jira Backlog Structure – Equipment Return

⸻

[Epic] Return – Start process
	•	[US1] Tablet action selection
	•	✅ “Equipment Return” button visible on home screen
	•	✅ Starts process when selected
	•	[US2] User support verification
	•	✅ System checks if user is supported
	•	✅ If supported + request exists → go to US3
	•	✅ If supported + no request → blank request created
	•	✅ If not supported → go to US2bis
	•	[US2bis] Non-supported user handling
	•	✅ Create blank incident in ServiceNow
	•	✅ Continue directly to US4

⸻

[Epic] Return – Requests handling
	•	[US3] Request verification and selection
	•	✅ Show list of open requests for the visitor
	•	✅ Technician must select one request
	•	✅ If no request → option to create a blank one
	•	✅ “Requalification” button available if wrong action
	•	✅ Button to search requests for another user
	•	✅ Form must display both depositor & owner
	•	[US3bis] Search requests for another user
	•	✅ Search field available
	•	✅ Technician can select a request from another user
	•	✅ System records depositor ≠ owner if different
	•	[US4] Automatic or manual form selection
	•	✅ If request already has type → auto-skip form selection
	•	✅ If new request → display list of forms (mandatory)
	•	✅ Selection logged

⸻

[Epic] Return – Equipment declaration
	•	[US5] Form completion
	•	✅ Pre-filled fields (name, surname, ID, equipment type, date, request date)
	•	✅ Depositor always displayed & modifiable
	•	✅ Internal depositor → searchable by ID/Name
	•	✅ External depositor → manual entry (name, surname, company, role)
	•	[US6] Equipment identification
	•	✅ 3 methods: barcode scan, list of assigned equipment, manual search/entry
	•	✅ Option to add “new unknown equipment” if not found
	•	[US6bis] StockRoom selection
	•	✅ If only one StockRoom → auto-selected
	•	✅ If multiple StockRooms → mandatory dropdown selection
	•	✅ Default = none selected

⸻

[Epic] Return – Verification & accessories
	•	[US7] Accessory selection
	•	✅ Display all possible accessories (tiles with pictures)
	•	✅ Technician selects returned ones
	•	✅ Always displayed, even if CMDB missing data
	•	[US8] Information verification
	•	✅ Show all captured information
	•	✅ Each section has an EDIT button
	•	✅ Validation button to confirm correctness
	•	[US8bis] Multiple equipment loop
	•	✅ System asks: “Do you have other equipment to return?”
	•	✅ If yes → select another request or create blank one
	•	✅ Process loops back to US4
	•	✅ If no → continue to US9

⸻

[Epic] Return – Validation & closure
	•	[US9] Global synthesis & signature
	•	✅ Display grouped by request (scrollable if multiple)
	•	✅ Depositor always displayed & modifiable
	•	✅ Signature required from both technician & depositor
	•	✅ Option to print report if depositor asks
	•	[US10] Automatic update & closure
	•	✅ Request/incident automatically updated with return info
	•	✅ Status set to Closed
	•	✅ All details logged and archived

⸻

👉 Avec ce format, tu peux directement copier-coller dans Jira :
	•	Les Epics comme parent containers
	•	Les US comme issues liées à l’Epic
	•	Les Acceptance Criteria comme checklist dans la description

⸻

Veux-tu que je t’en fasse une version tableau Markdown (Epic | US | Criteria) que tu pourrais importer ou coller dans Confluence/Jira pour une lecture ultra-visuelle ?
